**Course Reflection**

What were your initial expectations for the course? Did the course meet, exceed, or fall short of these expectations?

| I wanted SYSADM1 to provide a basic understanding of system administration, thus I had higher expectations for it in terms of practical tools and concepts. The training exceeded my expectations by giving me hands-on experience with topics like administering Windows servers and maintaining Git repositories. |
| :---- |

What were the main topics or concepts covered in the course? How did these topics contribute to your understanding of the subject matter?

| Web servers, Windows administration tools, and Git and GitHub repositories, Monitoring and creating our own network to fix the issue were, I believe, the primary subjects for me. My teamwork and management of versions skills were enhanced by Git and GitHub, and my understanding of web servers provided me with knowledge regarding hosting and managing internet enterprises. Windows Administrative Tools helped me better comprehend basic system management tasks, which boosted my confidence in handling real-world IT scenarios. |
| :---- |

Reflecting on your learning process, what were the most effective strategies or techniques that helped you grasp and retain the course material?

| The practical exercise was, in my opinion, the most effective method, especially when it comes to managing Git repositories and setting up web servers. This improved my understanding and study of the subjects as I worked with my peers and reviewed real-world case studies. |
| :---- |

Were there any particular assignments, projects, or activities that significantly enhanced your learning experience? Why were they effective?

| The web server configuration and monitoring work was the most beneficial to me. I was able to combine a number of skills, like using Windows Administrative Tools and platform services and investigating other systems, which improved my overall proficiency as an IT student and allowed me to practice my knowledge in practical settings. |
| :---- |

Did you encounter any challenges or difficulties during the course? How did you overcome these obstacles, and what did you learn from them?

| Troubleshooting problems with web server setups and printing services was one of the main challenges. I overcome this by employing trial-and-error techniques, reviewing internet documentation, and searching for peer help online. I learned from this how crucial perseverance and critical thought are to solving problems. |
| :---- |

Did the course encourage critical thinking and analysis? How did it promote higher-order thinking skills, such as problem-solving or decision-making?

| Yes, the course promoted critical thinking by pushing us to examine system issues and implement fixes. For instance, determining Printing Services, GIthub, and other tasks we perform require you to reflect more on what went wrong, weigh your options, and carry out repairs, all of which enhanced your analytical and decision-making skills. |
| :---- |

Reflecting on your personal growth, what new knowledge, skills, or perspectives did you gain from this course?

| I developed my technical abilities in using Windows Administrative Tools for system administration and setting up and maintaining web servers and setting up our Linux . Additionally, I became more aware of how crucial secure authentication techniques are to maintaining system integrity. |
| :---- |

How do you plan to apply what you have learned in this course to your future studies, career, or personal life?

| I intend to apply these skills in my upcoming IT initiatives, particularly in the areas of server administration and Git repository usage. As a future IT professional, these abilities will be essential to my ability to contribute to technical and collaborative work. |
